How necessary is it to have Pose Estimation? I have implementations to align with individual tags. Would there be a significant advantage to using global pose estimation instead?

Like a lot of engineering questions, it depends on your goals. Pose estimation and alignment are just one part of a particular points scoring strategy. “Better” is often relative.

If what you have is working, I personally wouldn’t bother changing at this point. Wait until the off-season to experiment with new things.

Depends on your end goals and your teams capability, knowing where your robot is on the field is great for odometry, aiming and other advanced features but if you aren’t getting reliable data there really is no strategic point to it all. Teams can often get in a trap of prioritizing optimizing things that already work well instead of looking at other underlying issues or begotten features of robot code (for example getting auto working while the PID on your elevator is broken).

If you have something that “just works” I would pay attention to other minor features (PID Tuning, Optimization, Auto, Etc) and then if you have time and the team is satisfied with its code move on to it and try it out (but definitely don’t spend a ton of time on it). The difference between solving where you are on the field versus using trigonometry for aiming / positioning with a tag is minimal and you definitely don’t need pose estimation to be competitive this year.

Hope that helps
